Definition:
When the method of superclass is overriden in subclass providing same method name and parameters is called method overriding.
Overriding methods can throw only checked exception.
_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Rules of overriding:
1)Method name and parameters should be same.
2)Child class method should have more or equal visiblity as compared to Parent class.
3)Private and Final methods cannot be overriden.
4)Must be in IS-A relationship.
5)We cannot override static methods.
6)Must follow all exception rules while overriding the methods.
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Why overriding ?
1)Code resubility
2)To change the existing behaviour of superclass method
3)To change the functionality.
